<h1><i class="fa fa-eye"></i>Viewing Files</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/working-with-files"><i class="fa fa-file"></i>Working with Files</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-eye"></i>Viewing Files</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p><%= application.name %> offers a number of ways to view your files and folders. These options allow you to view files in the most effective manner, whether you're viewing image files, code files, document files, music files, or other data files.</p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-eye"></i>The View Menu</h2>
			<p>To view the available options for viewing files and folders, mouse over the View menu on your <a href="#help/getting-started/using-desktop">Desktop</a> or <a href="#apps/file-browser">File Browser</a> window.

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropdown menu" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/view-menu2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">The View Menu</div>
			</div>
		</li>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-eye"></i>Appearance</h2>
			<p>The first set of options under the View menu is the appearance of files and folders.  You can select from the following options: </p>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-th icon"></i></span>Icons</h3>
					<p>Icons are the most common and are the default way to view files and folders. </p>
					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-icons.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Icons"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-icons.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Icons</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-align-left icon"></i></span>Names</h3>
					<p>Names are the most compact way to view files and folders and can be effective if you need to view a large number of items in a spall space.</p>
					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-names.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Names"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-names.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Names</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-list icon"></i></span>Lists</h3>
					<p>Lists are a clear and efficient way of viewing files that don't have a visual thumbnail representation, for example, code files or data files.</p>
					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-lists.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Lists"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-lists.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Lists</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-tree icon"></i></span>Trees</h3>
					<p>Trees are a an efficient way of viewing hierarchical collections of files and folders. To expand or collapse a subtree contained in a particular folder, click on the arrow expander icon to the left of the folder icon. </p>
					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-trees.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Trees"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-trees.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Trees</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-th-large icon"></i></span>Tiles</h3>
					<p>Tiles are the most effective way to view items that have thumbnail previews, such as image files or pdf files.  Note that when viewing items as tiles, you can change the size of the tiles using the size slider at the bottom right corner of the window. </p>
					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-tiles.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Tiles"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-tiles.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Tiles</div>
					</div>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3><span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-id-card"></i></span>Cards</h3>
					<p>Cards provide a clear way to view items with thumbnails and longer file names and are the default means of viewing files on mobile devices.</p>
					<div class="figure">
						<a href="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-cards.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Cards"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/working-with-files/viewing-files/file-browser-cards.png" /></a>
						<div class="caption">Cards</div>
					</div>
				</li>
			</ol>

		</li>
	</ol>
</div>